more then afore is limitted, hee shall forfayte
so much as hee taketh, and ten pound
more besides that, whereof the moyty shall
bee to the party greeued.
            If the Ordinary cite any person to appeare
in the Spirituall courte to depose in
any matter there, as a witnesse: that is extortion
aud wronge to the party.
            If any Ordinary; Person, or Uicar take
any mortuary after the death of any person
whych had not goods to the value of .x.
Markes, that is extortion. And lykewise it
is, where they take a mortuary in such places
where it hath not bene accustomed to
pay mortuaries. And euen so it is where
a Person, or Uicar taketh more then .iij.s.
iiij.d. in the name of a mortuary. If y• goods
amoūt aboue .x. markes, and vnder the value
of .xxx.li. for that is extortion.
